summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Twenty-fifth Avenue Northeast from East Fifty-fourth Street to Northern Pacific Railway Company right of way, all in the City of Seattle, by grading and curbing, in accordance with Resolution No. 522 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
